Here’s our next concrete move: plug in the snippet‑lookup into your generator. Roughly, in your `generateFunctionalEquivalent` step you’d swap out that big `switch` on `step.type` for something like:  
```js
function renderStep(step, targetLang) {
  const templates = index.languages
    .find(l => l.name === targetLang)
    .categories[step.type] || [];
  // pick a template (maybe the first or a random one)
  let snippet = templates[0] || `// no template for ${step.type}`;
  // now interpolate variable names, values, bodies, etc.
  snippet = snippet
    .replace(/\{\{name\}\}/g, step.name || '')
    .replace(/\{\{value\}\}/g, step.value || '');
  return snippet;
}
```
Then your loop becomes:  
```js
let generated = '';
for (const step of trace) {
  generated += renderStep(step, targetLang) + '\n';
}
setConvertedCode(generated);
```
